  "text": "The Andes are highly diverse in woody bamboo genera including the endemic genera Aulonemia, Arthrostylidium, Chusquea, Elytrostachys and Rhipidocladum, which are often associated with high-altitude forests and the Páramos (especially Chusquea and Aulonemia) [CITATION_1] Judziewicz et al. 1999) . According to these authors, 90% of the bamboo species in the Andes are endemic. Some groups of grasses which are especially rich in temperate regions and belong mainly to Poideae are also well represented in the region, such as Poa, Festuca, Piptochaetium, and Cortaderia.",
